Brother Gerald:<br><br>
I submit that the need for dehumanizing people before you kill them depends upon who you are and the circumstances that you are operating under.<br>
B-52s, Navy guns, tactical aircraft,heavy artillery pieces kill people at great distances.  People serving in this type warfare may be into enough denial or indoctrination to believe that they are.. &quot;engaging a target&quot;.. &quot;neutralizing a position&quot;... &quot;preparing a Landing Zone&quot;...&quot;conducting and offensive&quot;...&quot;securing a hill&quot;... &quot;doing a clearing operation&quot;... or one of the most absurd... &quot;harrassment and interdiction firing.&quot;  Bottom line:  They are trying to deal with the killing of people in a civil manner.  Fat chance!<br><br>
Perhaps a more barbaric but nontheless more honest approach, especially for those standing knee deep in human guts is to salvage some sanity by simply calling the enemy a bad name.  <br><br>
Don't ever kid yourself... the Civil War was filled with hatred on both sides...and sadness... and regret... and greed... and denial... and depersonalization.<br>
Interesting note:  Their name for PTSD was &quot;Soldier's Heart.&quot;<br><br>
With Respect,<br><br>
Ed
